<TITLE> Ward commissioner Chowdhury Alam gets 12 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Sunday sentenced Dhaka City Corporation ward commissioner Chowdhury Alam to 12 years in jail for extorting about Tk 24 crore. Judge KS Hawlader of Dhaka Metropolitan First Joint Sessions Judge's Court delivered the verdict before Alam, also a BNP leader. The court also fined the ward commissioner Tk 2 lakh or two more years in jail on failure to pay the fine. Alam's brother-in-law Rahmat Ali received a sentence of five years and Tk 1 lakh in fine in the same case. The court ordered one more year in jail for Ali in case he fails to pay the sum. Alam with Ali's assistance took Tk 23.93 crore in bribe for allocation of 2370 shops at Bangabazar complex between 2003 and 2005. The case was filed on May 1 last year with Shahbagh Police Station. Ali has been on the run. Prosecution lawyer Kabari Hossain said Alam received two sentences of 10 years each in two extortion cases and a further 13 years in a case filed by the Anticorruption Commission on charge of concealing information on wealth. bdnew
